  "prompt": "What do I do when I am lost in my life/Career? Read Description.",
  "response": "Here are some steps to help you when you feel lost in life or your career:\n\n1. Self-Reflection\n- Take time to understand yourself\n- Identify your passions, strengths, and values\n- Journal or meditate to gain clarity\n\n2. Assess Current Situation\n- Analyze what's working and what isn't\n- Identify specific areas of dissatisfaction\n- Recognize your skills and achievements\n\n3. Set Clear Goals\n- Create short-term and long-term objectives\n- Make SMART goals (Specific, Measurable, Achievable, Relevant, Time-bound)\n- Break larger goals into smaller, actionable steps\n\n4. Skill Development\n- Learn new skills related to your interests\n- Take online courses or workshops\n- Read books and attend seminars\n- Consider professional certifications\n\n5. Network and Seek Guidance\n- Connect with mentors\n- Attend industry events\n- Talk to professionals in fields you're interested in\n- Join professional groups or online communities\n\n6. Explore Options\n- Research different career paths\n- Consider job shadowing\n- Try informational interviews\n- Be open to potential career shifts\n\n7. Personal Development\n- Work on self-confidence\n- Practice self-care\n- Maintain a growth mindset\n- Seek therapy or career counseling if needed\n\n8. Take Action\n- Start small\n- Be consistent\n- Embrace calculated risks\n- Learn from failures\n\nRemember, feeling lost is temporary, and with purposeful action, you can find direction.",
